{"lemma": "شُفْعَةٌ", "slug": "شُفْعَةٌ", "root": "ش.ف.ع", "root_slug": "ش-ف-ع", "root_link": "/words/roots/ش-ف-ع", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n22640"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "pairing; right of pre-emption", "fa": "جفت; حق شفعه", "ur": "جوڑنا; حق شفعہ", "tr": "çift; şuf'a hakkı", "id": "pasangan; hak pre-emptif", "bn": "জোড়া; প্রি-এম্পশন অধিকার", "es": "emparejamiento; derecho de prelación", "fr": "appariement; droit de préemption", "de": "Paarung; Vorkaufsrecht", "ru": "пара; право преимущественной покупки", "zh": "配对; 优先购买权"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n22640", "headword_ar": "شُفْعَةٌ", "root": "$fE", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "is used in relation to a house and to land; (S, TA;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ufuEapN", "text_ar": "شُفُعَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with two dammehs, is a dial. var. thereof thus used. (TA.) It signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "milok", "text_ar": "مِلْك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[here meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "house,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "piece of land,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that is coupled"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ma$ofuwE", "text_ar": "مَشْفُوع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by purchase"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with one's"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "milok", "text_ar": "مِلْك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "house,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "piece of land, previously possessed, and adjoining thereto"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Mgh, Msb; *) from the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAna witorFA fa$afaEotuhu", "text_ar": "كَانَ وِتْرًا فَشَفَعْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[expl. above, in the second sentence of this art.]; (Mgh; [and the like is said in the Msb;]) a noun of the same class as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "luqomapN", "text_ar": "لُقْمَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; being of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuEolapN", "text_ar": "فُعْلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the sense of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mafoEuwlN", "text_ar": "مَفْعُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Mgh, Msb: *) this is the primary signification: then it was applied to denote"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a particular kind of obtaining possession;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh;) [i. e.] it is also used as meaning the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obtaining possession of that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "milok", "text_ar": "مِلْك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "house,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "piece of land, by purchasing it, and coupling it with that previously possessed, and adjoining thereto"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Msb;) or one's"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "making a demand respecting that which he seeks"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to possess, for the right of the pre-emption thereof"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and adjoining it to that which he"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "already"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K:) and with the lawyers it signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "right of obtaining possession of a piece of land,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "right of pre-emption thereof,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a house,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "against one's co-sharer whose possession is recent, by compulsion, for a compensation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "right of obtaining possession of a piece of land, by compulsion, for"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the payment of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what it cost the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "former"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "purchaser, by reason of partnership"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "immediate"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "neighbourship:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(KT:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "right of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "immediate"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "neighbourship with respect to"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pre-emption of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a house"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "land."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(PS.) [See 1 in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sqb", "text_ar": "سقب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] El-Kutabee says, in explaining this word, in the Time of Ignorance, when a man desired to sell a house, his neighbour used to come to him and to make a demand to him ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaEa", "text_ar": "شَفَعَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilayohi", "text_ar": "اـِلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Talaba", "text_ar": "طَلَبَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") respecting that which he sold [for the right of pre-emption], and he pronounced him to have a better right, or title, or claim, [as a purchaser,] to that which was sold, than he whose connexion was more remote: as though he took it from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~afaAEapu", "text_ar": "الشَّفَاعَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": but the [right] derivation is that first mentioned. (Mgh.) We have not heard, (Mgh,) or there is not known, (Msb,) any verb belonging to it [in the classical language]. (Mgh, Msb.) Esh-Shaabee uses it in the first and in the second of the senses expl. above, [or nearly so,] in his saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mano biyEato $ufoEatuhu wahuwa HaADirN falamo", "text_ar": "مَنْ بِيعَتْ شُفْعَتُهُ وَهُوَ حَاضِرٌ فَلَمْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaTolubo *`lika falaA $ufoEapa lahu", "text_ar": "يَطْلُبْ ذٰلِكَ فَلَا شُفْعَةَ لَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He whose claimed possession to be coupled by purchase with one already belonging to him is sold when he is present without his demanding that"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "possession,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "there shall be no obtaining possession for him by his purchasing it for that purpose"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mgh. [And the like is said in the Msb.]) Esh-Shaabee says [also],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~ufoEapu EalaY ruw^uwsi AlrijaAli", "text_ar": "الشُّفْعَةُ عَلَى رُوُوسِ الرِجَالِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The possession that is coupled by purchase with another possession is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "apportioned"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "according to the heads of the men"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "entitled thereto]: i. e., when the house is shared by a company of men whose shares are different, and one of them sells his portion, what is sold to his co-sharers is to be apportioned among them equally, according to their heads, not according to their [former] shares: (O, K, TA:) so in the Nh. (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ufoEapu AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "شُفْعَةُ الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The two rek'ahs"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakoEataAni", "text_ar": "رَكْعَتَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prayer that is performed in the period of the morning called the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DuHaY", "text_ar": "ضُحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlDHY", "text_ar": "الضحى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afoEapu", "text_ar": "شَفْعَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (O, K:) occurring in a trad., thus accord. to two different relations. (O.)       -A2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Diabolical,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "demoniacal, possession;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "madness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "insanity;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, O, K;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afoEapN", "text_ar": "شَفْعَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; the latter expl. in this sense by IAar; and as"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safoEapN", "text_ar": "سَفْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$unoEapN", "text_ar": "شُنْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rad~apN", "text_ar": "رَدَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naZorapN", "text_ar": "نَظْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [perceived] in the face: [see these words; the second and third of which generally mean"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an unseemliness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ugliness;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and so, sometimes, does the last:] the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ufoEapN", "text_ar": "شُفْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the sense here expl. on the authority of AA is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ufaEN", "text_ar": "شُفَعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And IF states that it has been said to signify The ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "evil"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "eye, by which one is smitten:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but he doubts its correctness; and thinks that it may be with the unpointed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (O.) [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safoEapN", "text_ar": "سَفْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sufoEapN", "text_ar": "سُفْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["O", "K", "KT", "Mgh", "Msb", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}